HEADWORD: Rocaille
<hw>Ro`caille"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. Cf.
<er>Rock</er> a stone.]</ety> <fld>(Art)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Artificial rockwork made of rough stones and cement, as for
gardens.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The rococo system of scroll ornament,
based in part on the forms of shells and water-worn rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

